climbs.name: Six Foot Girlfriend
climbs.fa: B. Li, J. Parkhill, D. Dao, 2019

content.description: Sit start and match hands on the crimp. Work the left and right point crimps up the face and out the roof. Match on the second ledge for finish.
content.protection: 1-2 pads with at least one spotter.
content.location: Start runs along the line 2-3ft off the ground. Foot chips may be hidden by the weeds.Â

content.description: Secluded area located along the railroad tracks across a clearing people use to dip in the lake. Perfect for the summer to escape the heat and heavy tourist traffic. Negative angle wall featuring plenty of crimps and a small roof section. Landing has some overgrown weeds, but very safe with a crash pad due to no rocks. This area offers a lot of potential to be explored.
